& [SLMClosedClassLexicalSenseRoutingContract] is the contract for routing open-class senses on closed-class tokens
  + [contract_uuid] is a42a4d85-86e7-43ac-b55a-07c1833f0f68
  + [slice_id] is SLM-38
  + [depends_on] is SLM_Closed_Class_Diffusion_Contract, SLM_Lexical_Sense_Evidence_Contract, SLM_Closed_Class_Role_Pair_Suppression_Contract
  + [status] is verified_wsl

  & [RoutingPrinciple] is how closed-class lexical senses should enter the evidence system
    = must: preserve source lexicon entries without deleting WordNet or database evidence
    = must: emit closed-class structural hints when closed-class authority exists
    = must: defer ordinary lexical sense suggestions for closed-class tokens by default
    = must: allow explicit routing policy to emit all senses for query and audit modes
    = must: treat deferred senses as routing discipline, not semantic collapse
    - never: convert a closed-class token into an open-class semantic glyph from raw lexical score alone

  & [ImplementationProjection] is the Rust source surface
    + [module] is slm_rust/src/lexicon.rs LexicalSenseRoutingPolicy
    + [module] is slm_rust/src/lexicon.rs LexicalSubstrateProvider::with_sense_routing_policy
    + [default_policy] is DeferClosedClassTokenSenses
    + [audit_policy] is EmitAllSenses
    + [verification] is WSL cargo test plus demo lexical sense inspection

  & [AcceptanceCriteria] is the behavioral proof target
    = must: article "a" emits determiner or structural evidence
    = must: article "a" does not emit ordinary lexical sense candidates in default demo output
    = must: explicit all-sense routing can still recover closed-class token senses
    = must: "Design a compiler for FPGA hardware." keeps lexical senses for open-class terms

  ! [Slice38SourceComplete] is accepted
    @ [source_gate] passed python slm_project/tools/slm_source_gate_check.py
    @ [wsl_cargo_test] passed 8 tests through CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/home/pinky/slm_rust_target and linker=/home/pinky/bin/zigcc
    @ [demo_proof] article token "a" produced 0 lexical sense candidates and one article/indefinite structural hint
    @ [demo_proof] open-class lexical sense terms remained design, compiler, hardware
